properties.sfomuseum:description: a. Airmail flight cover, Pan American Airways, fourth Pacific survey flight between California and Guam; blue stamped cachet at left, “First flight westbound to Guam” and green stamped cachet at center, “First flight eastbound from Guam”; postmarked October 5 and October 24, 1935 in San Francisco and October 16, 1935 in Guam with football-shaped and wavy cancellations over three 6-cent stamps; two backstamps: October 5, 1935 in Alameda and October 13, 1935 in Guam.b. Backing sheet with two sets of mounting corners, with handwritten caption: “October 1935, Pan American survey flight - San Francisco to Guam”, and black and white photographic image of Pan American Sikorsky S-42 on water.
